  <span id="freeText10011991444036858676" style="display:none">I read this when I was a kid, very young maybe 4th grade, and I loved it! It’s one of the books that I attribute to fueling my love of reading. I was already an avid reader but this is one of the earliest novels I still remember being fascinated with. I love historical fiction, maybe this was the start. Who knows.<br />It’s one of the first books I remember using my own money to buy because I wanted my own copy after reading the library’s. I looked at this to tag it to read again, haha, maybe I should let sleeping dogs lie happily. <br />Let kids books be kids books, good grief. Don’t berate people who appreciate things you do not. I also had a great many wonderful teachers growing up. How sad your experience is do different. <br /><br />Do you have suggestions for children’s novels that you approve of? Truly wondering!</span>
